{"key":"processedPost-7591004","value":{"id":7591004,"first":7590689,"last":7591004,"when":1194116434,"utime":"11/03/07 10:00 PM","content":"I doubt you'll get azures to fruit on pasteurized casing.  You'll want a slightly acid pH around 6 to 6.5, and some outdoor, non-pasteurized soil to provide the micro organisms.  Fruiting/primordia forming temps are best in the 50's.  Most growers fruit them outdoors for that reason.<br />RR","title":"Re: Correct pH for for casing P.azurescens (Hammond)?"}}